[dramatic music]

00:04:09.374 --> 00:04:11.501 position:50% align:center
- Koki is so enthusiastic.
- [exhales]

00:04:11.584 --> 00:04:13.211 position:50% align:center
- Most interns
don't usually work

00:04:13.294 --> 00:04:14.295 position:50% align:center
as hard as he does.
- [grunts]

00:04:14.379 --> 00:04:15.588 position:50% align:center
- He definitely doesn't act

00:04:15.672 --> 00:04:16.673 position:50% align:center
like he's the privileged heir

00:04:16.756 --> 00:04:18.299 position:50% align:center
of the Suido family.

00:04:18.383 --> 00:04:20.468 position:50% align:center
- Good point.

00:04:20.552 --> 00:04:22.554 position:50% align:center
- It's been three months.

00:04:22.637 --> 00:04:24.848 position:50% align:center
We've found zero clues
on Carneades

00:04:24.931 --> 00:04:27.642 position:50% align:center
and gotten no calls from Asumi.
- Hey, good work.

00:04:27.726 --> 00:04:29.227 position:50% align:center
- Mr. Chikushi.

00:04:29.310 --> 00:04:31.146 position:50% align:center
- Here's the intel
you asked me for.

00:04:31.229 --> 00:04:32.772 position:50% align:center
- This helps a lot.

00:04:32.856 --> 00:04:35.400 position:50% align:center
- This is all I can access
with my authorization level.

00:04:35.483 --> 00:04:37.652 position:50% align:center
- Thanks.
Sorry for asking so much.

00:04:37.736 --> 00:04:39.904 position:50% align:center
- Are you looking into
the Carneades case

00:04:39.988 --> 00:04:41.865 position:50% align:center
from the Hazard Cast front?
- Yes.

00:04:43.992 --> 00:04:45.785 position:50% align:center
- Information about Hazard Cast

00:04:45.869 --> 00:04:48.038 position:50% align:center
is top secret
even within S.A.R.G.,

00:04:48.121 --> 00:04:50.540 position:50% align:center
but your father could--
- It won't work like that.

00:04:50.623 --> 00:04:52.500 position:50% align:center
My father hates nepotism.

00:04:52.584 --> 00:04:54.085 position:50% align:center
- Ah, of course.

00:04:54.169 --> 00:04:55.712 position:50% align:center
Most people tend
to keep it secret

00:04:55.795 --> 00:04:57.255 position:50% align:center
when they bend the rules.

00:04:57.339 --> 00:04:59.758 position:50% align:center
But, well,
in that case,

00:04:59.841 --> 00:05:02.719 position:50% align:center
you need some experience, yeah?

00:05:02.802 --> 00:05:05.638 position:50% align:center
Since you're working so hard,
I'll toss you a special case.

00:05:05.722 --> 00:05:07.349 position:50% align:center
- Isn't this
the thing that's starting

00:05:07.432 --> 00:05:09.351 position:50% align:center
to gain popularity
around Shantytown?

00:05:09.434 --> 00:05:11.686 position:50% align:center
- Yeah, and it's something
S.A.R.G. wants

00:05:11.770 --> 00:05:14.105 position:50% align:center
to get under control
while we still can.

00:05:14.189 --> 00:05:16.149 position:50% align:center
Try working on it
with Hana's group.

00:05:17.776 --> 00:05:21.446 position:50% align:center
- So, Drug D.
- Over the past month,

00:05:21.529 --> 00:05:23.156 position:50% align:center
we've been working
with media outlets

00:05:23.239 --> 00:05:25.116 position:50% align:center
to highly publicize
the sudden increase

00:05:25.200 --> 00:05:26.701 position:50% align:center
of crime rates in Shantytown.

00:05:27.952 --> 00:05:29.371 position:50% align:center
I'm sure we'll start
hearing requests

00:05:29.454 --> 00:05:32.207 position:50% align:center
for redevelopment
from ward citizens soon.

00:05:32.290 --> 00:05:34.834 position:50% align:center
Mr. Howard,
the Casino King,

00:05:34.918 --> 00:05:37.379 position:50% align:center
we build a casino
in the 24th ward

00:05:37.462 --> 00:05:39.381 position:50% align:center
and we'll have succeeded
in building a casino

00:05:39.464 --> 00:05:41.383 position:50% align:center
in Japan as soon
as we're incorporated

00:05:41.466 --> 00:05:43.843 position:50% align:center
into Tokyo.
- Good.

00:05:43.927 --> 00:05:47.013 position:50% align:center
Then let's move the project
to the next phase.

00:05:47.097 --> 00:05:48.431 position:50% align:center
And as promised,

00:05:48.515 --> 00:05:50.266 position:50% align:center
you'll step aside allowing me

00:05:50.350 --> 00:05:52.811 position:50% align:center
to handle fundraising efforts
and clean house.

00:05:55.814 --> 00:05:57.774 position:50% align:center
- Very much obliged to you,
Mr. Howard.

00:05:57.857 --> 00:06:00.068 position:50% align:center
- You have arranged
for the goods?

00:06:00.151 --> 00:06:01.736 position:50% align:center
- Yes, I'll personally
bring them

00:06:01.820 --> 00:06:03.279 position:50% align:center
to you aboard the WINNER'S.

00:06:03.363 --> 00:06:04.989 position:50% align:center
- Don't let me down.

00:06:05.073 --> 00:06:07.826 position:50% align:center
- I promise you results
that are fitting for the cost.

00:06:09.494 --> 00:06:11.162 position:50% align:center
- [screams]

00:06:11.246 --> 00:06:12.872 position:50% align:center
The vape!
Where is the vape?

00:06:12.956 --> 00:06:15.500 position:50% align:center
- [humming]

00:06:15.583 --> 00:06:17.335 position:50% align:center
- Lucky, how are you doing?

00:06:17.419 --> 00:06:19.295 position:50% align:center
- ♪ One second ♪
- [gasps]

00:06:19.379 --> 00:06:21.589 position:50% align:center
Now he's starting
to thrash around a whole bunch!

00:06:21.673 --> 00:06:23.258 position:50% align:center
The withdrawal symptoms
for Drug D

00:06:23.341 --> 00:06:24.509 position:50% align:center
are beyond ridiculous!

00:06:24.592 --> 00:06:26.011 position:50% align:center
- There.
Got it.

00:06:26.094 --> 00:06:27.512 position:50% align:center
[booming]
- Huh?

00:06:27.595 --> 00:06:30.181 position:50% align:center
[groans]

00:06:31.224 --> 00:06:34.019 position:50% align:center
- Color me impressed.
Nicely done, Yamamori.

00:06:34.102 --> 00:06:35.937 position:50% align:center
That fight was a piece
of cake for you.

00:06:36.021 --> 00:06:37.856 position:50% align:center
- [panting]
- But he got back up.

00:06:37.939 --> 00:06:39.107 position:50% align:center
- [shouting]

00:06:39.190 --> 00:06:40.233 position:50% align:center
- [gasps]
- [grunts]

00:06:40.316 --> 00:06:42.402 position:50% align:center
Where's my vape?
Give it to me.

00:06:42.485 --> 00:06:44.446 position:50% align:center
- Let him go,
you strung-out bastard!

00:06:44.529 --> 00:06:46.239 position:50% align:center
All right, dude.
Let's talk.

00:06:46.322 --> 00:06:47.365 position:50% align:center
[stammering]
- [snarling]

00:06:47.449 --> 00:06:48.575 position:50% align:center
- Hang on.
- [growls]

00:06:48.658 --> 00:06:50.410 position:50% align:center
- [shouts]
- Ran, this is looking bad!

00:06:50.493 --> 00:06:52.537 position:50% align:center
- Hold on, Lucky!
Kinako, get out of the way!

00:06:52.620 --> 00:06:54.330 position:50% align:center
- What?
You've gotta be kidding me!

00:06:54.414 --> 00:06:55.665 position:50% align:center
[shouts]
[glass shatters]

00:06:55.749 --> 00:06:56.875 position:50% align:center
- [shouting]
- [grunts]

00:06:56.958 --> 00:06:59.878 position:50% align:center
[groans]

00:06:59.961 --> 00:07:01.296 position:50% align:center
[moaning]

00:07:01.379 --> 00:07:03.631 position:50% align:center
- Mm, dude's in no condition
to be questioned.

00:07:03.715 --> 00:07:06.468 position:50% align:center
- When's this guy gonna
be coming back to sanity, then?

00:07:06.551 --> 00:07:08.386 position:50% align:center
- Probably not for a while.

00:07:08.470 --> 00:07:10.930 position:50% align:center
- I'm not seeing anything in
this box that looks like a drug.

00:07:11.014 --> 00:07:13.308 position:50% align:center
- No pills, no powders,
no plants, no liquids.

00:07:13.391 --> 00:07:14.934 position:50% align:center
Nothing's stashed here.

00:07:15.018 --> 00:07:17.062 position:50% align:center
- A mysterious drug
that can't be found?

00:07:17.145 --> 00:07:18.271 position:50% align:center
Great.

00:07:18.355 --> 00:07:20.065 position:50% align:center
- Ran.
- Hmm?

00:07:20.148 --> 00:07:21.983 position:50% align:center
- It's S.A.R.G.
[distant sirens blaring]

00:07:22.067 --> 00:07:24.444 position:50% align:center
We should try to avoid 'em.

00:07:24.527 --> 00:07:26.988 position:50% align:center
- Hey, should we be taking
that junkie with us?

00:07:27.072 --> 00:07:29.199 position:50% align:center
- No, this is one case
where we can't--

00:07:29.282 --> 00:07:30.867 position:50% align:center
- Drug D.
- Yeah.

00:07:30.950 --> 00:07:33.328 position:50% align:center
- How has it spread so much
in such a short time?

00:07:33.411 --> 00:07:35.622 position:50% align:center
Feels like someone must
be pullin' strings

00:07:35.705 --> 00:07:36.664 position:50% align:center
in the background.

00:07:36.748 --> 00:07:38.291 position:50% align:center
- [groans]
Drug D.

00:07:38.375 --> 00:07:40.418 position:50% align:center
I won't tolerate it.

00:07:40.502 --> 00:07:42.087 position:50% align:center
- Hey, what gives, Ran?

00:07:42.170 --> 00:07:44.130 position:50% align:center
- Huh?
- Where are you going?

00:07:44.214 --> 00:07:46.883 position:50% align:center
- Huh?
The elevator moves now?

00:07:46.966 --> 00:07:48.885 position:50% align:center
When this old piece
of junk get fixed?

00:07:48.968 --> 00:07:50.679 position:50% align:center
- Sometime this month,
I think.

00:07:50.762 --> 00:07:52.597 position:50% align:center
- Why after so long, though?

00:07:52.681 --> 00:07:54.349 position:50% align:center
Somebody's whimsical,
I see.

00:07:54.432 --> 00:07:56.351 position:50% align:center
Kunai's grandma has a bad leg

00:07:56.434 --> 00:07:58.019 position:50% align:center
so I suppose
it helps her out a ton.

00:08:00.105 --> 00:08:03.608 position:50% align:center
- Now that I think of it,
I haven't seen Kunai in a while.

00:08:03.692 --> 00:08:04.776 position:50% align:center
- Yeah.

00:08:04.859 --> 00:08:06.444 position:50% align:center
Apparently he's been developing

00:08:06.528 --> 00:08:07.904 position:50% align:center
a new type of mobile app.

00:08:07.987 --> 00:08:10.490 position:50% align:center
We still text now and then.

00:08:10.573 --> 00:08:12.117 position:50% align:center
He's always been the type
that doesn't show up

00:08:12.200 --> 00:08:13.660 position:50% align:center
for a while once he bunks down.

00:08:20.750 --> 00:08:22.377 position:50% align:center
- I'm going out now.
- Huh?

00:08:22.460 --> 00:08:24.337 position:50% align:center
Oh, you take care, then.

00:08:24.421 --> 00:08:26.089 position:50% align:center
Please make sure
to hurry home before

00:08:26.172 --> 00:08:28.133 position:50% align:center
it gets too dark out,
all right?

00:08:28.216 --> 00:08:30.844 position:50% align:center
- Yeah.
I'll be back soon.

00:08:30.927 --> 00:08:33.263 position:50% align:center
- Shuta, get ready
to close up shop!

00:08:33.346 --> 00:08:35.306 position:50% align:center
- Yeah, yeah.

00:08:35.390 --> 00:08:37.517 position:50% align:center
Oh, hey, Mari.
You, too?

00:08:37.600 --> 00:08:39.269 position:50% align:center
Yeah.
Mom's stepping out,

00:08:39.352 --> 00:08:40.895 position:50% align:center
so we're closing shop for today.

00:08:40.979 --> 00:08:42.647 position:50% align:center
- I see.
[grunts]

00:08:42.731 --> 00:08:43.732 position:50% align:center
Hmm?

00:08:43.815 --> 00:08:45.734 position:50% align:center
Oh, is that Kozue?

00:08:45.817 --> 00:08:47.235 position:50% align:center
- Yeah, that's Kozue.

00:08:47.318 --> 00:08:48.653 position:50% align:center
Come to think of it,

00:08:48.737 --> 00:08:50.572 position:50% align:center
I've heard she's been going out
at night lately.

00:08:50.655 --> 00:08:51.948 position:50% align:center
- Ah?
From who?

00:08:52.032 --> 00:08:53.825 position:50% align:center
- From Shirakaba's wife.

00:08:53.908 --> 00:08:56.703 position:50% align:center
I bumped into her the other day.

00:08:56.786 --> 00:08:58.621 position:50% align:center
- [groans]

00:08:58.705 --> 00:09:01.291 position:50% align:center
Mrs. Kaba, huh?
How's she doing?

00:09:01.374 --> 00:09:03.293 position:50% align:center
- She's lost a lot of weight,

00:09:03.376 --> 00:09:05.503 position:50% align:center
but it seems like she
was getting by.

00:09:05.587 --> 00:09:07.255 position:50% align:center
- I see.

00:09:07.339 --> 00:09:09.674 position:50% align:center
- Well, I'm worried,
so I'm gonna go after her.

00:09:09.758 --> 00:09:11.718 position:50% align:center
- Wait a sec!
- Uh?

00:09:11.801 --> 00:09:13.011 position:50% align:center
What?
- You would be in danger, too.

00:09:13.094 --> 00:09:14.804 position:50% align:center
- Uh, but...

00:09:14.888 --> 00:09:17.307 position:50% align:center
Fine, then you can go instead
of me, Shu.

00:09:17.390 --> 00:09:19.309 position:50% align:center
- Uh--
[groans]

00:09:20.560 --> 00:09:21.853 position:50% align:center
Fine.
I'll go.

00:09:25.523 --> 00:09:26.649 position:50% align:center
Kozue!
- [gasps]

00:09:26.733 --> 00:09:27.609 position:50% align:center
- Where are you going?

00:09:29.319 --> 00:09:31.446 position:50% align:center
It's dangerous to go out alone.
- You're right.

00:09:31.529 --> 00:09:33.948 position:50% align:center
A suspicious person
is following me as we speak.

00:09:34.032 --> 00:09:35.241 position:50% align:center
- Huh?
Who, me?

00:09:35.325 --> 00:09:36.951 position:50% align:center
- I will scream, Shu.
- What?

00:09:37.035 --> 00:09:39.037 position:50% align:center
I'm just worried about you,
Kozue.

00:09:39.120 --> 00:09:41.039 position:50% align:center
If you're going somewhere,
I'll come with.

00:09:41.122 --> 00:09:43.291 position:50% align:center
- Leave me alone!
- Oh, hey!

00:09:43.375 --> 00:09:46.252 position:50% align:center
[groans]
Come on.

00:09:46.336 --> 00:09:47.712 position:50% align:center
There's no way
I can leave her alone.

00:09:47.796 --> 00:09:48.922 position:50% align:center
[distant car horn honking]

00:09:49.005 --> 00:09:51.966 position:50% align:center
- Hey, Kozue,
I said I'd tag along,

00:09:52.050 --> 00:09:53.802 position:50% align:center
but this place is sketchy.

00:09:53.885 --> 00:09:55.053 position:50% align:center
[dogs snarling]

00:09:55.136 --> 00:09:58.640 position:50% align:center
Really, Kozue.
It's not for kids.

00:09:58.723 --> 00:10:00.100 position:50% align:center
This place is bad news.

00:10:00.183 --> 00:10:02.102 position:50% align:center
Shantytown is no joke.

00:10:02.185 --> 00:10:04.604 position:50% align:center
- Then feel free to go home
by yourself, Shu.

00:10:04.688 --> 00:10:06.356 position:50% align:center
- [gasps]
- I have something to do here.

00:10:06.439 --> 00:10:09.567 position:50% align:center
- Something to do?
Does it have to be right now?

00:10:09.651 --> 00:10:11.569 position:50% align:center
- Hey, mister.
Up for some fun?

00:10:11.653 --> 00:10:13.571 position:50% align:center
- Oh, no, thank you.

00:10:13.655 --> 00:10:14.739 position:50% align:center
- Don't come onto guys
with kids.

00:10:14.823 --> 00:10:17.325 position:50% align:center
- Oh, by the way,
would you like a rusk?

00:10:17.409 --> 00:10:19.285 position:50% align:center
- What's with that?
- I thought I'd offer 'cause

00:10:19.369 --> 00:10:20.787 position:50% align:center
you like rusks, right?

00:10:20.870 --> 00:10:23.289 position:50% align:center
- I'm not a kid anymore,
so why are you baiting me?

00:10:26.042 --> 00:10:27.877 position:50% align:center
What is with you tonight?

00:10:27.961 --> 00:10:30.213 position:50% align:center
Why have you been stalking me?

00:10:30.296 --> 00:10:33.216 position:50% align:center
- Oh, well, I thought,
you know--

00:10:33.299 --> 00:10:34.676 position:50% align:center
- Is it atonement?

00:10:36.052 --> 00:10:37.929 position:50% align:center
- No, it's not...

00:10:41.683 --> 00:10:43.435 position:50% align:center
- You didn't need to swoop in
to save me.

00:10:43.518 --> 00:10:45.437 position:50% align:center
- [gasps]
Kozue.

00:10:45.520 --> 00:10:47.814 position:50% align:center
What did you just say?

00:10:47.897 --> 00:10:49.399 position:50% align:center
- I should have been
the one to die instead,

00:10:49.482 --> 00:10:50.650 position:50% align:center
not him!
- Hey, wait!

00:10:50.734 --> 00:10:54.362 position:50% align:center
[panting]

00:10:54.446 --> 00:10:56.489 position:50% align:center
Huh?
Where did she go?

00:10:56.573 --> 00:10:59.492 position:50% align:center
[exhales]
Dammit.

00:10:59.576 --> 00:11:03.455 position:50% align:center
- [shouting growing closer]
- [gasps]

00:11:03.538 --> 00:11:05.665 position:50% align:center
Hey, are you all right?
- Hey, mister!

00:11:05.749 --> 00:11:07.542 position:50% align:center
- [gasps]
- Yes, you, down there!

00:11:07.625 --> 00:11:10.420 position:50% align:center
Pin that guy down till we
can come and cuff him!

00:11:10.503 --> 00:11:12.839 position:50% align:center
[gasps]
You're that Shuta Aoi kid!

00:11:12.922 --> 00:11:15.425 position:50% align:center
- She's from S.A.R.G.
[both grunting]

00:11:15.508 --> 00:11:17.093 position:50% align:center
- [grunts]
Don't let him get away!

00:11:17.177 --> 00:11:19.220 position:50% align:center
He's a drug dealer!
- What?

00:11:19.304 --> 00:11:22.349 position:50% align:center
- [grunting]

00:11:22.432 --> 00:11:24.309 position:50% align:center
- Dammit!
This is insane!

00:11:24.392 --> 00:11:25.894 position:50% align:center
Why do I have to do this?

00:11:25.977 --> 00:11:27.437 position:50% align:center
- [panting]

00:11:27.520 --> 00:11:28.438 position:50% align:center
- [screams]
- Hey!

00:11:28.521 --> 00:11:30.857 position:50% align:center
- [panting]

00:11:30.940 --> 00:11:32.442 position:50% align:center
Hey, wait up!

00:11:32.525 --> 00:11:34.778 position:50% align:center
[grunting]

00:11:34.861 --> 00:11:37.072 position:50% align:center
- [shouting]
Out of the way!

00:11:37.155 --> 00:11:38.990 position:50% align:center
[shouting]

00:11:39.074 --> 00:11:40.158 position:50% align:center
[thuds]
[groans]

00:11:40.241 --> 00:11:42.452 position:50% align:center
- [panting]
What?

00:11:42.535 --> 00:11:43.536 position:50% align:center
Koki?
- Shu?

00:11:43.620 --> 00:11:45.080 position:50% align:center
Why are you chasing after
this guy?

00:11:45.163 --> 00:11:46.498 position:50% align:center
- [groaning]

00:11:46.581 --> 00:11:48.416 position:50% align:center
- I don't know.
That's how things ended up.

00:11:48.500 --> 00:11:50.919 position:50% align:center
The scary S.A.R.G. lady told me
to do it.

00:11:51.002 --> 00:11:53.505 position:50% align:center
That guy, he's a drug dealer,
isn't he?

00:11:53.588 --> 00:11:55.006 position:50% align:center
- Yes, that's right.

00:11:55.090 --> 00:11:57.759 position:50% align:center
This man sells
the mysterious Drug D.

00:11:57.842 --> 00:11:59.177 position:50% align:center
- Drug D?

00:11:59.260 --> 00:12:01.554 position:50% align:center
- It's an illicit drug
that's highly addictive.

00:12:01.638 --> 00:12:03.306 position:50% align:center
What it is is still a mystery,

00:12:03.390 --> 00:12:06.226 position:50% align:center
but its users lose their sense
of judgment and become violent.

00:12:06.309 --> 00:12:07.811 position:50% align:center
Due to this,

00:12:07.894 --> 00:12:09.771 position:50% align:center
the crime rate in Shantytown
has been skyrocketing

00:12:09.854 --> 00:12:11.022 position:50% align:center
for the past month.

00:12:11.106 --> 00:12:13.358 position:50% align:center
- Well, that isn't good.
Oh, wait.

00:12:13.441 --> 00:12:15.944 position:50% align:center
That might be
what Kozue's here for.

00:12:16.027 --> 00:12:18.655 position:50% align:center
She's been wandering
around Shantytown recently.

00:12:18.738 --> 00:12:19.823 position:50% align:center
That's why I'm here.

00:12:19.906 --> 00:12:21.116 position:50% align:center
I followed her tonight
and then--

00:12:21.199 --> 00:12:22.701 position:50% align:center
- You lost sight of her?

00:12:22.784 --> 00:12:24.911 position:50% align:center
- Yeah.
- Let's find her.

00:12:24.994 --> 00:12:26.037 position:50% align:center
You take the north side.

00:12:26.121 --> 00:12:27.288 position:50% align:center
- What?
S--Sure.

00:12:27.372 --> 00:12:28.248 position:50% align:center
- Hey, Mr. Shindo?

00:12:31.376 --> 00:12:32.836 position:50% align:center
Regardless of Drug D,

00:12:32.919 --> 00:12:34.295 position:50% align:center
Shantytown isn't
a place she should

00:12:34.379 --> 00:12:36.089 position:50% align:center
be wandering around alone.

00:12:36.172 --> 00:12:38.675 position:50% align:center
Hazard Cast doesn't work
in this part of the ward.

00:12:38.758 --> 00:12:40.093 position:50% align:center
- Huh?

00:12:40.176 --> 00:12:41.720 position:50% align:center
- Hazard Cast
calculates predictions

00:12:41.803 --> 00:12:43.555 position:50% align:center
of crime scenes
automatically based

00:12:43.638 --> 00:12:45.306 position:50% align:center
on data collected within
the city.

00:12:46.266 --> 00:12:48.018 position:50% align:center
Shantytown--
with so many old buildings--

00:12:48.101 --> 00:12:50.311 position:50% align:center
has few surveillance cameras,

00:12:50.395 --> 00:12:52.022 position:50% align:center
and cPhones
with sensors aren't given

00:12:52.105 --> 00:12:53.732 position:50% align:center
to illegal immigrants.

00:12:53.815 --> 00:12:55.775 position:50% align:center
- It's completely useless.

00:12:55.859 --> 00:12:57.444 position:50% align:center
- Like a certain someone
right now.

00:12:57.527 --> 00:12:58.695 position:50% align:center
- [groans]

00:12:58.778 --> 00:13:00.155 position:50% align:center
- That's exactly why this town

00:13:00.238 --> 00:13:01.489 position:50% align:center
needs redevelopment.

00:13:01.573 --> 00:13:03.742 position:50% align:center
It needs monitoring
and registration

00:13:03.825 --> 00:13:06.369 position:50% align:center
and management via cPhones.

00:13:06.453 --> 00:13:07.620 position:50% align:center
- Well, now that
you bring it up,

00:13:07.704 --> 00:13:10.081 position:50% align:center
I feel like that's sort
of scary.

00:13:10.165 --> 00:13:12.334 position:50% align:center
It's like someone's watching you
at all times.

00:13:12.417 --> 00:13:13.793 position:50% align:center
Doesn't that seem weird?

00:13:13.877 --> 00:13:16.296 position:50% align:center
- That's such
an antiquated complaint.

00:13:16.379 --> 00:13:18.340 position:50% align:center
Data sent from cPhones
is encrypted

00:13:18.423 --> 00:13:20.759 position:50% align:center
so personal information
is under protection.

00:13:20.842 --> 00:13:22.635 position:50% align:center
Is it heroic to let
a vague sense

00:13:22.719 --> 00:13:25.347 position:50% align:center
of uneasiness stop you
from saving somebody?

00:13:25.430 --> 00:13:27.098 position:50% align:center
What if yet again someone dear
to you--

00:13:27.182 --> 00:13:28.475 position:50% align:center
- Okay, I get it!
- [gasps]

00:13:29.976 --> 00:13:31.269 position:50% align:center
- Seriously, I get it.

00:13:33.480 --> 00:13:36.358 position:50% align:center
[tense music]

00:13:36.441 --> 00:13:39.110 position:50% align:center
[both chuckling]

00:13:42.739 --> 00:13:43.782 position:50% align:center
- [gasps]

00:13:43.865 --> 00:13:45.450 position:50% align:center
[giggles]

00:13:45.533 --> 00:13:47.494 position:50% align:center
- Hey.
- [gasps]

00:13:47.577 --> 00:13:49.913 position:50% align:center
- Why are you here?
You lookin' for Drug D?

00:13:49.996 --> 00:13:51.623 position:50% align:center
- Huh?
Drug D?

00:13:51.706 --> 00:13:53.917 position:50% align:center
No.
No, I'm not.

00:13:54.000 --> 00:13:55.585 position:50% align:center
I'm here for this.

00:13:55.669 --> 00:14:02.092 position:50% align:center
♪ ♪

00:14:04.177 --> 00:14:06.596 position:50% align:center
- Kozue,
where did you run off to?

00:14:06.680 --> 00:14:08.807 position:50% align:center
- Oh, hey, Shu.
- Huh?

00:14:08.890 --> 00:14:10.141 position:50% align:center
- It's been a while,
hasn't it?

00:14:10.225 --> 00:14:12.102 position:50% align:center
- Oh, long time no see, Ran.

00:14:12.185 --> 00:14:14.688 position:50% align:center
Although you're not who
I'm looking for right now.

00:14:14.771 --> 00:14:16.523 position:50% align:center
- You haven't had enough
of hero work?

00:14:16.606 --> 00:14:18.358 position:50% align:center
- Huh?
Oh, it's not like that.

00:14:18.441 --> 00:14:20.151 position:50% align:center
I'm searching for Kozue.

00:14:20.235 --> 00:14:22.612 position:50% align:center
- For Kozue?
- I got separated from her.

00:14:22.696 --> 00:14:23.988 position:50% align:center
- That's dangerous.

00:14:24.072 --> 00:14:26.741 position:50% align:center
Hold on a sec.
I can ask my crew.

00:14:26.825 --> 00:14:28.785 position:50% align:center
Oh, Kunai's taking care of her.

00:14:28.868 --> 00:14:29.994 position:50% align:center
- Who is Kunai?

00:14:30.078 --> 00:14:31.996 position:50% align:center
- A part
of our super brilliant crew.

00:14:32.080 --> 00:14:33.164 position:50% align:center
Don't worry.
She's good.

00:14:33.248 --> 00:14:34.624 position:50% align:center
- Oh, seriously?

00:14:34.708 --> 00:14:35.917 position:50% align:center
What a lifesaver.
[phone trilling]

00:14:36.001 --> 00:14:37.502 position:50% align:center
[exhales]
Such a relief.

00:14:37.585 --> 00:14:38.753 position:50% align:center
I'm glad.

00:14:38.837 --> 00:14:40.714 position:50% align:center
Oh, I need to let Koki know,
too.

00:14:42.590 --> 00:14:44.217 position:50% align:center
[trilling continues]

00:14:44.300 --> 00:14:46.261 position:50% align:center
- Hey, Kunai.

00:14:46.344 --> 00:14:48.304 position:50% align:center
Been a while.
Haven't seen you at DoRed.

00:14:48.388 --> 00:14:49.305 position:50% align:center
Somethin' up?

00:14:50.807 --> 00:14:53.143 position:50% align:center
- It's nothing.
Just same old, same old.

00:14:54.477 --> 00:14:56.021 position:50% align:center
- Gotcha.

00:14:56.104 --> 00:14:58.106 position:50% align:center
Well, if you need anything,
contact me, okay?

00:14:59.399 --> 00:15:01.443 position:50% align:center
- Sounds good.
See you later.

00:15:01.526 --> 00:15:03.111 position:50% align:center
- Hey, Shu!
- Huh?

00:15:03.194 --> 00:15:04.779 position:50% align:center
- You showed up at a good time.

00:15:04.863 --> 00:15:06.573 position:50% align:center
You mind taggin' along
for a little bit?

00:15:07.949 --> 00:15:09.075 position:50% align:center
[camera shutter clicks]

00:15:09.159 --> 00:15:11.411 position:50% align:center
- So you were looking
for graffiti?

00:15:11.494 --> 00:15:13.329 position:50% align:center
- I knew it
when I saw it online.

00:15:13.413 --> 00:15:14.789 position:50% align:center
I said to myself,
"Hey, look.

00:15:14.873 --> 00:15:16.166 position:50% align:center
That's my dad."

00:15:16.249 --> 00:15:17.417 position:50% align:center
Everybody in the comments

00:15:17.500 --> 00:15:19.586 position:50% align:center
was calling him Kaba
or Mr. Kaba.

00:15:19.669 --> 00:15:23.673 position:50% align:center
Besides, these pieces have only
started being drawn recently,

00:15:23.757 --> 00:15:25.675 position:50% align:center
ever since the GourFes tornado.

00:15:26.843 --> 00:15:28.678 position:50% align:center
- So that's why you came here.

00:15:28.762 --> 00:15:31.222 position:50% align:center
- I want to know who drew them.

00:15:31.306 --> 00:15:33.808 position:50% align:center
Hey, would you happen to know?

00:15:35.685 --> 00:15:38.104 position:50% align:center
- It's DoRed's leader.
It's Red.

00:15:38.188 --> 00:15:39.898 position:50% align:center
- [gasps]
So you do know!

00:15:39.981 --> 00:15:42.025 position:50% align:center
Where can I find him?

00:15:42.108 --> 00:15:44.319 position:50% align:center
- Can't tell you,
even if I knew.

00:15:44.402 --> 00:15:46.488 position:50% align:center
- Why not?

00:15:46.571 --> 00:15:49.157 position:50% align:center
- You know the story
of "The Wizard of Oz?"

00:15:49.240 --> 00:15:51.201 position:50% align:center
The Wizard
and his alias spread across

00:15:51.284 --> 00:15:54.788 position:50% align:center
the land of Oz by keeping
his true identity a secret.

00:15:54.871 --> 00:15:57.290 position:50% align:center
- Well, I understand
I can't meet him,

00:15:57.374 --> 00:16:00.085 position:50% align:center
but tell me.
What kind of person is Red?

00:16:01.252 --> 00:16:02.921 position:50% align:center
- He's a genius artist.

00:16:04.005 --> 00:16:08.093 position:50% align:center
A child born in Shantytown only
has two futures to dream of.

00:16:08.176 --> 00:16:10.720 position:50% align:center
One is to become a criminal

00:16:10.804 --> 00:16:13.348 position:50% align:center
and rule over
the town with money,

00:16:13.431 --> 00:16:15.892 position:50% align:center
and the other
is to become an artist

00:16:15.975 --> 00:16:17.644 position:50% align:center
and get out of this town.

00:16:17.727 --> 00:16:19.145 position:50% align:center
Red is the latter.

00:16:19.229 --> 00:16:20.939 position:50% align:center
Ever since he was very young,

00:16:21.022 --> 00:16:23.274 position:50% align:center
everyone expected him
to be an artist.

00:16:23.358 --> 00:16:26.945 position:50% align:center
His talent was so overwhelming.
Everyone acknowledged it.

00:16:27.028 --> 00:16:30.323 position:50% align:center
- But graffiti's a crime,
isn't it?

00:16:30.407 --> 00:16:33.243 position:50% align:center
- People say that Shantytown
is a dangerous place

00:16:33.326 --> 00:16:35.453 position:50% align:center
and claim it's in need
of redevelopment, right?

00:16:35.537 --> 00:16:37.914 position:50% align:center
- Yeah, they want to make it
a casino

00:16:37.997 --> 00:16:40.709 position:50% align:center
and let the government control
the area and make it safer?

00:16:40.792 --> 00:16:43.837 position:50% align:center
- Some fish can only live
in murky waters.

00:16:43.920 --> 00:16:46.297 position:50% align:center
If the tank is changed
to clean the water,

00:16:46.381 --> 00:16:49.759 position:50% align:center
the fish no longer have
a place to hide and are eaten,

00:16:49.843 --> 00:16:53.096 position:50% align:center
but nobody listens to the voices
of those living in shadows.

00:16:53.179 --> 00:16:55.015 position:50% align:center
- So unfair.

00:16:55.098 --> 00:16:57.642 position:50% align:center
- Red continues to draw graffiti
on the streets

00:16:57.726 --> 00:17:01.312 position:50% align:center
for all of us in Shantytown who
are in that situation.

00:17:01.396 --> 00:17:04.065 position:50% align:center
To change
the world through his art.

00:17:04.149 --> 00:17:07.110 position:50% align:center
- He wants to change
the world through art?

00:17:07.193 --> 00:17:10.530 position:50% align:center
But that's just not possible.
I don't believe it.

00:17:10.613 --> 00:17:13.116 position:50% align:center
- Trust me.
Red'll do it someday.

00:17:13.199 --> 00:17:15.452 position:50% align:center
He's a genius artist,
after all.

00:17:21.458 --> 00:17:23.460 position:50% align:center
[spray can rattling]
- [exhales sharply]

00:17:23.543 --> 00:17:26.421 position:50% align:center
[dramatic piano music]

00:17:26.504 --> 00:17:28.798 position:50% align:center
♪ ♪

00:17:28.882 --> 00:17:30.050 position:50% align:center
- Here.
- Hmm?

00:17:30.133 --> 00:17:32.594 position:50% align:center
Ah, danke schoen.

00:17:32.677 --> 00:17:34.471 position:50% align:center
- You do this kind
of thing every night?

00:17:34.554 --> 00:17:35.889 position:50% align:center
- Yeah, dude.

00:17:35.972 --> 00:17:38.391 position:50% align:center
And this is the last
of a whole series.

00:17:38.475 --> 00:17:41.144 position:50% align:center
So, what do you think
of Super Kaba?

00:17:41.227 --> 00:17:43.605 position:50% align:center
♪ ♪

00:17:43.688 --> 00:17:45.899 position:50% align:center
- It's undeniable.
Kaba's a true hero.

00:17:45.982 --> 00:17:50.737 position:50% align:center
♪ ♪

00:17:50.820 --> 00:17:53.406 position:50% align:center
You know,
I've been so terrified.

00:17:55.492 --> 00:17:58.328 position:50% align:center
Like, what should I do
if we get another call?

00:17:58.411 --> 00:18:00.372 position:50% align:center
I might end up losing
someone dear to me again.

00:18:02.374 --> 00:18:03.583 position:50% align:center
Why's it gotta be me?

00:18:05.335 --> 00:18:06.920 position:50% align:center
Better off
in someone else's hands.

00:18:08.171 --> 00:18:10.382 position:50% align:center
I start meddling
and then screw up.

00:18:11.925 --> 00:18:13.093 position:50% align:center
I feel like a fool.

00:18:16.137 --> 00:18:19.057 position:50% align:center
- The reason why Shantytown
has such a high crime rate

00:18:19.140 --> 00:18:20.975 position:50% align:center
is because
of prejudices coinciding

00:18:21.059 --> 00:18:23.269 position:50% align:center
with the data set.

00:18:23.353 --> 00:18:25.647 position:50% align:center
The number guys
in S.A.R.G. calculate

00:18:25.730 --> 00:18:28.233 position:50% align:center
crime rates
from reported statistics.

00:18:28.316 --> 00:18:30.985 position:50% align:center
If someone from Shantytown
and someone from somewhere else

00:18:31.069 --> 00:18:32.696 position:50% align:center
are walkin' side by side,

00:18:32.779 --> 00:18:35.824 position:50% align:center
they'll definitely approach us
for questioning.

00:18:35.907 --> 00:18:38.451 position:50% align:center
And then the S.A.R.G. department
treats us like criminals.

00:18:38.535 --> 00:18:40.286 position:50% align:center
So Shantytown's crime rate
goes up

00:18:40.370 --> 00:18:41.955 position:50% align:center
and leads
to authorities intensifying

00:18:42.038 --> 00:18:43.790 position:50% align:center
their patrols.

00:18:43.873 --> 00:18:45.583 position:50% align:center
It begs the question,

00:18:45.667 --> 00:18:48.336 position:50% align:center
which came first:
the chicken or the egg?

00:18:48.420 --> 00:18:51.715 position:50% align:center
The thing that creates crime
isn't data, though.

00:18:51.798 --> 00:18:54.801 position:50% align:center
It's the hearts of the people
who look at the data.

00:18:54.884 --> 00:18:57.345 position:50% align:center
So even if you're relying
on Hazard Cast,

00:18:57.429 --> 00:19:00.765 position:50% align:center
that only fortifies rules
of the world as it stands now.

00:19:00.849 --> 00:19:02.600 position:50% align:center
If you want to change the world,

00:19:02.684 --> 00:19:05.061 position:50% align:center
you have
to change people's hearts.

00:19:05.145 --> 00:19:07.022 position:50% align:center
And that's exactly why...

00:19:08.565 --> 00:19:09.733 position:50% align:center
I use this thing.

00:19:11.776 --> 00:19:13.153 position:50% align:center
- That's so awesome.

00:19:14.237 --> 00:19:15.321 position:50% align:center
- [chuckles]

00:19:24.164 --> 00:19:25.790 position:50% align:center
- Changin' the world, huh?

00:19:25.874 --> 00:19:27.792 position:50% align:center
Jeez.

00:19:27.876 --> 00:19:29.794 position:50% align:center
- Today's is so big.
- Huh?

00:19:29.878 --> 00:19:30.879 position:50% align:center
[Junya Enoki, Yuma Uchida,
and Kaito Ishikawa's

00:19:30.962 --> 00:19:31.963 position:50% align:center
"255,255,255"]

00:19:32.047 --> 00:19:33.298 position:50% align:center
- Kozue?

00:19:33.381 --> 00:19:34.466 position:50% align:center
- I heard from a friend

00:19:34.549 --> 00:19:36.343 position:50% align:center
a new art piece
was going up here.

00:19:36.426 --> 00:19:38.345 position:50% align:center
- Oh, I get it.

00:19:38.428 --> 00:19:41.264 position:50% align:center
This piece
is titled "Super Kaba."

00:19:41.348 --> 00:19:43.975 position:50% align:center
- That's so literal.
[camera shutter clicks]

00:19:44.059 --> 00:19:45.769 position:50% align:center
- Got a pic?

00:19:45.852 --> 00:19:46.978 position:50% align:center
- Yeah.
Look.

00:19:48.897 --> 00:19:50.565 position:50% align:center
- Sweet.

00:19:50.648 --> 00:19:52.525 position:50% align:center
Hang on.
You have others?

00:19:52.609 --> 00:19:54.944 position:50% align:center
Oh, you're walkin' around
because you were looking

00:19:55.028 --> 00:19:57.614 position:50% align:center
for Kaba art.
- Well, yeah.

00:19:57.697 --> 00:20:01.201 position:50% align:center
But why do you think he bothers
doing something like this?

00:20:01.284 --> 00:20:04.079 position:50% align:center
All of his effort is meaningless
if they get erased.

00:20:04.162 --> 00:20:06.122 position:50% align:center
- Mm...

00:20:06.206 --> 00:20:07.582 position:50% align:center
That's not true.

00:20:07.665 --> 00:20:09.584 position:50% align:center
Even if it's erased,
it'll still remain.

00:20:10.752 --> 00:20:12.253 position:50% align:center
It's not meaningless because you

00:20:12.337 --> 00:20:14.297 position:50% align:center
and I will know
that someone drew this,

00:20:14.381 --> 00:20:16.424 position:50% align:center
and we'll remember somebody
like this existed.

00:20:16.508 --> 00:20:19.386 position:50% align:center
- [singing in Japanese]

00:20:19.469 --> 00:20:21.721 position:50% align:center
♪ ♪

00:20:21.805 --> 00:20:24.099 position:50% align:center
- Listen.
How do I say this?

00:20:26.309 --> 00:20:27.852 position:50% align:center
Please don't
ever say stuff like

00:20:27.936 --> 00:20:31.773 position:50% align:center
you should have died
in his place, okay?

00:20:31.856 --> 00:20:33.400 position:50% align:center
Please?

00:20:33.483 --> 00:20:35.276 position:50% align:center
- Well, then,
in that case, Shu?

00:20:35.360 --> 00:20:36.528 position:50% align:center
- Yeah?

00:20:36.611 --> 00:20:39.447 position:50% align:center
[all singing in Japanese]

00:20:39.531 --> 00:20:40.740 position:50% align:center
♪ ♪

00:20:40.824 --> 00:20:42.701 position:50% align:center
- [groans]

00:20:42.784 --> 00:20:45.120 position:50% align:center
Don't stop protecting me ever,
okay?

00:20:47.747 --> 00:20:49.499 position:50% align:center
You're like my big brother, Shu.

00:20:51.292 --> 00:20:53.003 position:50% align:center
Actually, you're my hero.

00:20:53.086 --> 00:20:54.379 position:50% align:center
[laughing]

00:20:56.631 --> 00:20:57.632 position:50% align:center
- Yeah, absolutely.

00:20:59.759 --> 00:21:00.885 position:50% align:center
Of course I would.

00:21:02.345 --> 00:21:05.306 position:50% align:center
'Cause I'm a student
of Super Kaba.

00:21:06.850 --> 00:21:08.476 position:50% align:center
- Yep, you are.

00:21:08.560 --> 00:21:12.397 position:50% align:center
[dramatic music]

00:21:12.480 --> 00:21:14.858 position:50% align:center
- Want a rusk?
- [laughs]

00:21:14.941 --> 00:21:16.359 position:50% align:center
Sure.
[crunches]

00:21:16.443 --> 00:21:17.902 position:50% align:center
It's good.

00:21:17.986 --> 00:21:20.071 position:50% align:center
- We put a lot
of time into baking that rye.

00:21:20.155 --> 00:21:21.823 position:50% align:center
It's got fiber,
minerals,

00:21:21.906 --> 00:21:23.450 position:50% align:center
and beauty benefits.

00:21:23.533 --> 00:21:25.910 position:50% align:center
- Shu,
you really haven't changed.

00:21:25.994 --> 00:21:26.995 position:50% align:center
- [chuckles]
What do you mean?

00:21:27.078 --> 00:21:28.329 position:50% align:center
[lights buzzing]
Hmm?

00:21:28.413 --> 00:21:29.581 position:50% align:center
What the?

00:21:29.664 --> 00:21:31.833 position:50% align:center
- It's just like in a movie.

00:21:31.916 --> 00:21:33.335 position:50% align:center
- What is that?

00:21:33.418 --> 00:21:36.296 position:50% align:center
[suspenseful music]

00:21:36.379 --> 00:21:39.799 position:50% align:center
♪ ♪

00:21:39.883 --> 00:21:43.178 position:50% align:center
[buzzing]
- Choose your future.

00:21:43.261 --> 00:21:46.431 position:50% align:center
Choose your destiny.

00:21:46.514 --> 00:21:49.309 position:50% align:center
Choose your future.

00:21:49.392 --> 00:21:50.685 position:50% align:center
- It's that image.

00:21:50.769 --> 00:21:52.979 position:50% align:center
- Carneades.

00:21:53.063 --> 00:21:54.647 position:50% align:center
- Wait a sec.

00:21:54.731 --> 00:21:56.941 position:50% align:center
That's the guy
people say started the tornado.

00:21:57.025 --> 00:21:58.943 position:50% align:center
- It'll  be okay.
[phone beeping]

00:21:59.027 --> 00:22:01.321 position:50% align:center
All right,
I still have service.

00:22:01.404 --> 00:22:04.866 position:50% align:center
- So, it looks like this
is a challenge from Carneades.

00:22:04.949 --> 00:22:07.243 position:50% align:center
- The guy's not subtle about
his performances.

00:22:07.327 --> 00:22:08.703 position:50% align:center
- Both of you listen to me.

00:22:08.787 --> 00:22:10.789 position:50% align:center
Last time we didn't have time
to talk it out,

00:22:10.872 --> 00:22:12.540 position:50% align:center
but if all three
of us had worked together

00:22:12.624 --> 00:22:13.792 position:50% align:center
as a team I'm sure we would

00:22:13.875 --> 00:22:15.669 position:50% align:center
have ended up
with a different outcome!

00:22:15.752 --> 00:22:17.796 position:50% align:center
- It's so like you
to think that, Shu,

00:22:17.879 --> 00:22:19.589 position:50% align:center
but it was a coincidence
we arrived

00:22:19.673 --> 00:22:22.092 position:50% align:center
at a third solution during
the bit with the Kizuna.

00:22:22.175 --> 00:22:24.260 position:50% align:center
- Events might veer towards
the unexpected

00:22:24.344 --> 00:22:25.804 position:50% align:center
just like last time
this happened.

00:22:25.887 --> 00:22:27.555 position:50% align:center
If us three fail again--

00:22:27.639 --> 00:22:29.766 position:50% align:center
- Yeah, but still.
I can't bear to abandon someone.

00:22:29.849 --> 00:22:32.185 position:50% align:center
[phones buzzing]

00:22:32.268 --> 00:22:34.229 position:50% align:center
[all gasping]

00:22:34.312 --> 00:22:36.481 position:50% align:center
Here it is.
From Asumi.

00:22:36.564 --> 00:22:37.524 position:50% align:center
You ready?

00:22:37.607 --> 00:22:38.858 position:50% align:center
- Yeah.
- Mm.

00:22:41.277 --> 00:22:45.115 position:50% align:center
[buzzing]

00:22:47.033 --> 00:22:49.994 position:50% align:center
- A luxurious cruise ship
is sailing through Tokyo Bay.

00:22:51.955 --> 00:22:53.998 position:50% align:center
VIPs are aboard this ship,

00:22:54.082 --> 00:22:57.419 position:50% align:center
and a terrorist has planted
a remote control bomb on it.

00:22:58.503 --> 00:23:01.214 position:50% align:center
There is only one way
to stop this crime.

00:23:01.297 --> 00:23:04.759 position:50% align:center
Will you sniper the perpetrator
and kill him to stop

00:23:04.843 --> 00:23:05.969 position:50% align:center
the ship from exploding?

00:23:08.013 --> 00:23:09.973 position:50% align:center
Or will you let him go...

00:23:11.016 --> 00:23:14.102 position:50% align:center
And as a result
let many people die

00:23:14.185 --> 00:23:15.812 position:50% align:center
from the exploding cruise ship?

00:23:15.895 --> 00:23:17.564 position:50% align:center
[flames roaring]

00:23:17.647 --> 00:23:20.066 position:50% align:center
Guide the future.

00:23:20.150 --> 00:23:22.861 position:50% align:center
[buzzing]

00:23:26.406 --> 00:23:28.199 position:50% align:center
- Another trolley dilemma.

00:23:28.283 --> 00:23:30.118 position:50% align:center
- There isn't any room
for debate.

00:23:30.201 --> 00:23:32.328 position:50% align:center
I refuse to abandon
those innocent victims

00:23:32.412 --> 00:23:33.788 position:50% align:center
and succumb to terrorism.

00:23:33.872 --> 00:23:35.999 position:50% align:center
- This isn't even really
two choices.

00:23:36.082 --> 00:23:38.877 position:50% align:center
- You think this
is a trick question?

00:23:38.960 --> 00:23:41.463 position:50% align:center
- That terrorist
who got shot dead...

00:23:41.546 --> 00:23:43.381 position:50% align:center
It was...

00:23:43.465 --> 00:23:44.883 position:50% align:center
Kunai?

00:23:44.966 --> 00:23:47.302 position:50% align:center
- When a child's born
in Shantytown,

00:23:47.385 --> 00:23:49.220 position:50% align:center
they only have
two possible futures

00:23:49.304 --> 00:23:51.139 position:50% align:center
to dream of achieving.

00:23:51.222 --> 00:23:53.933 position:50% align:center
One future
is to become a criminal

00:23:54.017 --> 00:23:56.436 position:50% align:center
and rule over
this town with money,

00:23:56.519 --> 00:23:58.688 position:50% align:center
and the other
is to become an artist

00:23:58.772 --> 00:24:01.024 position:50% align:center
and break away from here.

00:24:01.107 --> 00:24:04.611 position:50% align:center
As somebody with zero talent
as an artist, I--

00:24:04.694 --> 00:24:09.157 position:50% align:center
[laughing]

00:24:09.240 --> 00:24:11.326 position:50% align:center
My future is--
[gasps]